<doc>
  <member name="D3D12_INPUT_CLASSIFICATION">
    <summary>
      <para>Identifies the type of data contained in an input slot.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>Specify one of these values in the member of a <see cref="D3D12_INPUT_ELEMENT_DESC" /> structure to specify the type of data for the input element of a pipeline state object.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d12/direct3d-12-enumerations">Core Enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_INPUT_CLASSIFICATION.D3D12_INPUT_CLASSIFICATION_PER_VERTEX_DATA">
    <summary>
      <para>Input data is per-vertex data.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_INPUT_CLASSIFICATION.D3D12_INPUT_CLASSIFICATION_PER_INSTANCE_DATA">
    <summary>
      <para>Input data is per-instance data.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>